# Frontend — Next.js 14 + Tailwind

Source: [awesome-cursorrules — cursorrules-cursor-ai-nextjs-14-tailwind-seo-setup](https://github.com/PatrickJS/awesome-cursorrules)

- Use the **App Router** under `app/`; Server Components by default; `'use client'` only when interactivity or browser-only APIs require it.
- **Tailwind** for styling; avoid inline styles unless necessary.
- **TypeScript** everywhere; props via `interface`; named exports for shared components; **default export** for `page.tsx` / `layout.tsx` as per Next conventions.
- **Metadata API** (`export const metadata`) for SEO titles and descriptions.
- Use **next/image** with dimensions/lazy loading where appropriate.
- **fetch** in Server Components with `next: { revalidate }` (or cache options) when calling HTTP APIs.
- Add **`loading.tsx`** and **`error.tsx`** (and error boundaries) for route-level UX.
- **Route handlers** in `route.ts` for App Router APIs when needed; prefer calling the separate FastAPI backend for core product APIs unless the PRD says otherwise.
- Accessibility: semantic HTML, labels, keyboard support; align with WCAG when building UI.
- Prefer inferred types; avoid redundant `React.FC` unless it clarifies children or generics.
